TY  - JOUR
AU  - L’Huillier, Jean-Paul
AU  - Singh, Sanjay R
AU  - Yoo, Donghoon
T1  - Incorporating Diagnostic Expectations into the New Keynesian Framework
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdad101
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 91
IS  - 5
SP  - 3013
EP  - 3046
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Diagnostic expectations constitute a realistic behavioural model of inference. This paper shows that this approach to expectation formation can be productively integrated into the New Keynesian framework. Diagnostic expectations generate endogenous extrapolation in general equilibrium. We show that diagnostic expectations generate extra amplification in the presence of nominal frictions; a fall in aggregate supply generates a Keynesian recession; fiscal policy is more effective at stimulating the economy. We perform Bayesian estimation of a rich medium-scale model that incorporates consensus forecast data. Our estimate of the diagnosticity parameter is in line with previous studies. Moreover, we find empirical evidence in favour of the diagnostic model. Diagnostic expectations offer new propagation mechanisms to explain fluctuations.
Y2  - 10/27/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdad101
ER  - 



